{
  "stem": "3659.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We absolutely melted and died and crawled within ourselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "No, we were never, ever hit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one day my father talked to me about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he said, I was beaten so terribly as a child because my father believed that you cannot only love, you also have to punish.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he punished me so severely by beating me that I swore when I have children, never will I lay a hand on them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was the truth.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He never ever did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And for many, many years, he held it against his father, that he did that to him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And for all the Jewish holidays, we always went to visit the relatives, his father in Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "For the high holidays, for Yom Kippur and Rosh Hashanah we went there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I remember once or twice we also went for Pesach, for Passover.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I still remember the synagogue in Zywiec, where the ladies were all sitting upstairs, and the men were sitting downstairs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the men were all dressed in white when it came during Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the women used to bring the apples, and they-- they put little things into the apples to smell them so that your hunger wouldn't be so big during that time.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So you remember that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember the young man that used to blow-- blow the shofar so that nobody could wait that the-- the sun would set so he can blow it so everybody could go home and eat.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So these are some of the memories that I have.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I-- my grandfather was a very, very tall man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was about 6 foot 2'', but he had infantile paralysis, which nobody could realize at that time, and he always needed help in walking.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
